Extracting Media off of Device

In the app, click on Camera to see all your footage that’s not transferred - click on the circle of the photo or video that you want to transfer. It will transfer to your phone.

On your Computer, if you have a mac, transfer it from ImageCapture onto your phone and it should transfer in equirectangular mode
From there, you can pull into Premiere or AfterEffects and edit it like any other video.

You can also download Ricoh Theta’s desktop application and connect your Ricoh Theta to your computer and drag the footage off of the device into the program. The program will format the footage and export it as equirectangular 

